“ As for ourselves, in the ingenuity of our conscience, we herein do not decline the judgment of any indifferent impassionate man3 and such we hope this true and plain narration will satisfy. But above all, according to our duty and desire, we humbly submit this and all other our actions, concerning our calling, to thejudg- ment of our most venerahle mother the Church of England, from whose sacred rule we avow we have not swerved, nor any whit impeached her discipline, or authorized doctrine, either abroad or at home.
